kets, <a class=\"ml-smartlink\" href=\"http://www.people.com/people/jonas_brothers\">Jonas Brothers</a> Tickets, Coldplay Tickets, Concert Tickets, Super Bowl Tickets, NFL Tickets, New England Patriots Tickets, Celine Dion Tickets, World Series Tickets, Led Zeppelin. VetTix is the Internet&lsquo;s best source for premium sports, concert, and theater tickets. Vet Tix provides consumers a safe and easy way to purchase tickets to the world&rsquo;s top events. Vet Tix sales directly help Veterans. We are a national non-profit, non-governmental 501c(19) tax-exempt organization.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.chaserescorlafund.org/\">Chase Rescorla Scholarship Fund</a> was established in honor of Pfc. Leo C. Chase Jr. and Lt. <a class=\"ml-smartlink\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rick_Rescorla\">Rick Rescorla</a>, two brave soldiers with connections to St. Augustine who sacrificed their lives in service to our country.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.anyveteran.org/siteimages/servicedogs.jpg\" style=\"width: 240px; height: 160px; float: left; margin: 8px;\" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://patriotservicedogs.org/\">PatriotServiceDogs.org</a> Patriot <a class=\"ml-smartlink\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Service_dog\">Service Dogs</a>, Inc is a 501(c)(3) organization dedicated to helping Florida&#39;s disabled community gain a sense of independence through their partnership with a well trained service dog. Our focus is placing <a class=\"ml-smartlink\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Service_dog\">service dogs</a> with returning Veterans in need. We strive to make a difference in the lives of those who have given so much for our freedom. We were formed in July of 2009 in Central Florida with initial offices in Jacksonville &amp; Belleview.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.anyveteran.org/siteimages/patch-fm-150-w.jpg\" style=\"width: 200px; height: 200px; float: left; margin: 8px 10px;\" /></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.cvmaflorida.org/index.html\">Combat Veterans Motorcycle Association</a> We are an Association of Combat Veterans from all branches of the United States Armed Forces who ride motorcycles as a hobby. Our mission is to support and defend those who have defended our country and our freedoms. Our focus is to help veteran care facilities provide a warm meal, clothing, shelter, and guidance, or simply to say &quot;Thank you&quot; and &quot;Welcome home&quot;! Our membership is comprised of Full Members with verified combat service. We sponsor and participate in many motorcycle-related charity events each year and donate to various veteran care facilities and veteran charities. We are a 501(c) (19) Tax Exempt, non-profit organization which means that all donations are tax deductable.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://www.anyveteran.org/siteimages/174banner.jpg\" style=\"width: 640px; height: 182px; \" /><br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.174ahc.org/index.html\">174th Assault Helicopter Company</a> formed at Ft. Benning, GA in 1965 and deployed all personnel and equipment to Vietnam by U.S. Navy ships in 1966, landing at the Vietnamese port at the city of Qui Nhon. The unit&#39;s three primary &quot;homes&quot; in Vietnam were Lane Army Heliport near Qui Nhon (1966; II-Corps), Duc Pho in Quang Ngai Province (1967-1970; I-Corps), and <a class=\"ml-smartlink\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chu_Lai\">Chu Lai</a>, basecamp for the Americal Division (1971; also I-Corps). The 174th flew various models of the UH-1 &quot;Huey&quot; helicopter. The unit served long and proud in Vietnam and saw much combat action in the rice paddies and mountains in the northern half of South Vietnam from 1966 until 1971, and in Laos during <a class=\"ml-smartlink\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Operation_Lam_Son_719\">Operation Lam Son 719</a> in 1971. The website is dedicated to those Dolphins and Sharks, both pilots and enlisted crew-members - brave men all - who did not return.</p>\r\n', 0, '1', '1', '1', 0, '1', '1', '1', '2011-08-09 11:28:17', '2011-08-09 11:28:17', 0, NULL, '0', NULL);
